The paper focuses on the data processing capabilities of blockchain systems, which suggests a strong connection to database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses cryptography and consensus protocols, which are common topics in computer security (cs.CR). The evaluation of blockchain systems against data processing workloads involves analyzing their distributed nature, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses smart contracts, which are a key feature of blockchain systems and are often implemented using software engineering principles (cs.SE).
